The '''German Broadcasting Archive''' (''Deutsches Rundfunkarchiv''; DRA) is a non-profit foundation supported by the [[ARD (broadcaster)|ARD]]. It was founded in 1952 as "German sound archive". The DRA covers essential aspects of the development of German broadcasting. Today it has two locations: [[Frankfurt|Frankfurt am Main]] and [[Potsdam-Babelsberg]] (formerly Berlin-Adlershof).
