{{Infobox Website | name = Luminous-Lint | logo = | screenshot = | caption = | url = [http://www.luminous-lint.com www.luminous-lint.com] | commercial = no | type = Online database on photography | language = {{en icon}} | registration = | owner = | author = | launch date = December 5th, 2005 | current status = Active | revenue = }}
'''Luminous-Lint''' (or '''Luminous Lint''') is a website on photography, run by Alan Griffiths,<ref>"[https://www.photolucida.org/current_reviewers.php Critical Mass Jurors 2007]", photolucida.org. Accessed 2010-12-27.</ref> on vintage and contemporary photography.<ref>[http://slantoflight.org/2011/05/postcard-from-the-past/ Slant of Light] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110606120815/http://slantoflight.org/2011/05/postcard-from-the-past/ |date=2011-06-06 }}</ref> The site also serves as a collaborative knowledge base on the history of photography and includes some 60,000 photographs, 700 online exhibitions, biographies of more than 7,000 photographers, and information about techniques, galleries and dealers, photography timelines and other photography-related issues.<ref name="photowings">{{cite web|url=http://www.photowings.org/pages/index.php?rcA2324|title=Luminous-Lint|language=|publisher=PhotoWings.org|accessdate=2010-12-19}}</ref> Robert Hirsch has referred to it as a "top-notch" photographic site.<ref>Robert Hirsch, ''Light and Lens: Photography in the Digital Age'' (Amsterdam: Elsevier; Boston: Focal Press, 2007; {{ISBN|0-240-80855-X}}), p.329-330; [https://books.google.com/books?id=l3NB0gxtW5wC&amp;pg=PA330#v=onepage&amp;q&amp;f=false here] at [[Google Books]] (accessed 2010-12-27).</ref>
The site reproduces ''Photo Synthesis'', a series of articles on individual works that [[Colin Westerbeck]] first contributed to the ''[[Los Angeles Times]].''<ref>''[http://www.luminous-lint.com/app/blob/Colin__Westerbeck_01/1/ Photo Synthesis]'' series at Luminous-Lint; [http://www.luminous-lint.com/app/blob/Colin__Westerbeck_01/ Westerbeck's introduction] to the series.</ref>
